<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="429" pageId="11" pageNumber="428" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[802,1159,1159,1248]" box="[824,1137,1222,1248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">
(
<figureCitation box="[831,896,1222,1248]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[151,162,1607,1624]" captionTargetBox="[518,1171,965,1472]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 3. — Spiral sculpture (apertural view); A, Chicoreus (Siratus) consuela (Verrill, 1950), Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls; B-D, C. (S.) ciboney (Clench &amp; Pérez Farfante, 1945); B, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), four whorls; C, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), five whorls; D, Port- Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls. For A and D, the siphonal canal is not completely drawn. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5400578" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5400578/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">Figs 3</figureCitation>
B-D; 4C; 6A; 8A; 9E)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[714,1248,1287,1666]" box="[714,859,1287,1313]" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[714,1248,1287,1666]" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Clench &amp; Perez Farfante" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[714,866,1319,1346]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Chicoreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="428" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ciboney" subGenus="Siratus">
<emphasis box="[714,739,1319,1345]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[755,775,1319,1345]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[792,866,1320,1346]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">ciboney</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Merle &amp; Garrigues &amp; Pointier, 2001" authorityName="Merle &amp; Garrigues &amp; Pointier" authorityYear="2001" box="[1007,1180,1319,1346]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Chicoreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="428" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="guionneti" status="n. sp." subGenus="Siratus">
<emphasis box="[1007,1032,1319,1345]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1048,1068,1319,1345]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1085,1180,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">guionneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1188,1247,1319,1345]" pageId="11" pageNumber="428" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and the other studied species in having a multispiral protoconch of three whorls (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1142,1384,1410]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[151,162,805,822]" captionTargetBox="[213,1179,152,783]" captionTargetId="figure-445@11.[197,1192,139,803]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 8. — Protoconchs and first teleoconch whorl; A, Chicoreus (Siratus) ciboney (Clench &amp; Pérez Farfante, 1945), Port-Louis; B, C. (S.) guionneti n. sp., Martinique; C, C. (S.) cailleti (Petit de la Saussaye, 1856), Saba bank; D, C. (S.) perelegans Vokes, 1965, Port-Louis; E, C. (S.) articulatus (Reeves, 1845), Puerto Cortes; F, C. (S.) consuela (Verrill, 1950), Port-Louis. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5400588" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5400588/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
), suggesting a planktotrophic larval development. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Clench &amp; Perez Farfante" baseAuthorityYear="1945" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Chicoreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="428" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ciboney" subGenus="Siratus">
<emphasis box="[1174,1200,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1217,1238,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[714,790,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">ciboney</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has thicker primary and secondary cords (
<figureCitation box="[722,785,1480,1506]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[151,162,1607,1624]" captionTargetBox="[518,1171,965,1472]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 3. — Spiral sculpture (apertural view); A, Chicoreus (Siratus) consuela (Verrill, 1950), Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls; B-D, C. (S.) ciboney (Clench &amp; Pérez Farfante, 1945); B, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), four whorls; C, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), five whorls; D, Port- Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls. For A and D, the siphonal canal is not completely drawn. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5400578" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5400578/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B-D), developed but low intervarical nodules (
<figureCitation box="[771,855,1512,1538]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[151,162,1564,1581]" captionTargetBox="[223,1169,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[205,1146,177,1560]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 6. — Profile views of the intervarical nodules; A, Chicoreus (Siratus) ciboney (Clench &amp; Pérez Farfante, 1945), Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls; B, C. (S.) perelegans Vokes, 1965, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), six whorls; C, C. (S.) consuela (Verrill, 1950), Port- Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls; D, C. (S.) articulatus (Reeves, 1845), Porto Rico (coll. Garrigues), seven whorls; E, C. (S.) formosus (Sowerby, 1841), Haiti (coll. Garrigues); F, C. (S.) guionneti n. sp., Martinique (paratype, MNHN); G, C. (S.) cailleti (Petit de la Saussaye, 1856), Saintes (coll. Lamy), seven whorls. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5400584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5400584/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
) which are present on the strongest secondary cords (s3, s4), shorter or absent spines in the adult morphology (
<figureCitation box="[981,1074,1576,1602]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[151,162,1564,1581]" captionTargetBox="[223,1169,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[205,1146,177,1560]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 6. — Profile views of the intervarical nodules; A, Chicoreus (Siratus) ciboney (Clench &amp; Pérez Farfante, 1945), Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls; B, C. (S.) perelegans Vokes, 1965, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), six whorls; C, C. (S.) consuela (Verrill, 1950), Port- Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls; D, C. (S.) articulatus (Reeves, 1845), Porto Rico (coll. Garrigues), seven whorls; E, C. (S.) formosus (Sowerby, 1841), Haiti (coll. Garrigues); F, C. (S.) guionneti n. sp., Martinique (paratype, MNHN); G, C. (S.) cailleti (Petit de la Saussaye, 1856), Saintes (coll. Lamy), seven whorls. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5400584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5400584/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
), and denticles within the outer lip. This species occurs from 
<collectingCountry box="[714,772,1640,1666]" name="Cuba" pageId="11" pageNumber="428">Cuba</collectingCountry>
to Lesser Antilles in 200 to 300 meters deep.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[184,651,166,224]" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">
<taxonomicName authority="Vokes, 1965" authorityName="Vokes" authorityYear="1965" box="[184,651,166,194]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Chicoreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="429" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perelegans" subGenus="Siratus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,508,166,194]" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,290,168,194]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">Chicoreus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[306,383,166,192]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">Siratus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[399,508,168,194]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">perelegans</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Vokes, 1965
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[265,330,198,224]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1607,1624]" captionTargetBox="[207,1173,177,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-96@4.[162,1146,170,1583]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Spiral sculpture (apertural view); A-C, Chicoreus (Siratus) perelegans Vokes, 1965; A, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), four whorls; B, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), five whorls; C, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), six whorls; D, C. (S.) consuela (Verrill, 1950), Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), six whorls. The siphonal canal is not completely drawn. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5400576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5400576/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">Figs 2</figureCitation>
A-C; 4A; 6B; 8D; 9H)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,684,263,578]" box="[151,296,263,289]" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,684,263,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vokes" authorityYear="1965" box="[151,337,295,322]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Chicoreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="429" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perelegans" subGenus="Siratus">
<emphasis box="[151,176,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[194,215,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[233,337,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">perelegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the association of thick primary and secondary cords s3, s4 (
<figureCitation box="[159,226,360,386]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[151,162,1607,1624]" captionTargetBox="[207,1173,177,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-96@4.[162,1146,170,1583]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 2. — Spiral sculpture (apertural view); A-C, Chicoreus (Siratus) perelegans Vokes, 1965; A, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), four whorls; B, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), five whorls; C, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), six whorls; D, C. (S.) consuela (Verrill, 1950), Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), six whorls. The siphonal canal is not completely drawn. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5400576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5400576/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A-C), the absence of intervarical nodules (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,392,418]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[151,162,1564,1581]" captionTargetBox="[223,1169,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-147@8.[205,1146,177,1560]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 6. — Profile views of the intervarical nodules; A, Chicoreus (Siratus) ciboney (Clench &amp; Pérez Farfante, 1945), Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls; B, C. (S.) perelegans Vokes, 1965, Port-Louis (coll. Lamy), six whorls; C, C. (S.) consuela (Verrill, 1950), Port- Louis (coll. Lamy), seven whorls; D, C. (S.) articulatus (Reeves, 1845), Porto Rico (coll. Garrigues), seven whorls; E, C. (S.) formosus (Sowerby, 1841), Haiti (coll. Garrigues); F, C. (S.) guionneti n. sp., Martinique (paratype, MNHN); G, C. (S.) cailleti (Petit de la Saussaye, 1856), Saintes (coll. Lamy), seven whorls. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5400584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5400584/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
), short or absent spines, only two intervarical ribs, and stronger inner denticles of the outer lip than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Merle &amp; Garrigues &amp; Pointier, 2001" authorityName="Merle &amp; Garrigues &amp; Pointier" authorityYear="2001" box="[331,503,455,482]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Chicoreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="429" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="guionneti" status="n. sp." subGenus="Siratus">
<emphasis box="[331,357,455,481]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[372,392,455,481]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[407,503,456,481]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">guionneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[510,568,455,481]" pageId="12" pageNumber="429" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
This character association is not found in 
<taxonomicName authority="Merle &amp; Garrigues &amp; Pointier, 2001" authorityName="Merle &amp; Garrigues &amp; Pointier" authorityYear="2001" box="[508,684,487,514]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Chicoreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="429" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="guionneti" status="n. sp." subGenus="Siratus">
<emphasis box="[508,533,487,513]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[550,570,487,513]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[588,684,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">guionneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,212,519,545]" pageId="12" pageNumber="429" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vokes" authorityYear="1965" box="[220,401,519,546]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Chicoreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="429" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perelegans" subGenus="Siratus">
<emphasis box="[220,245,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[263,283,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[300,401,520,546]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">perelegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[597,653,520,546]" name="Haiti" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">Haiti</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[151,250,552,578]" name="Barbados" pageId="12" pageNumber="429">Barbados</collectingCountry>
between 80 and 120 meters deep.
</paragraph>
